3), his break-through, La Haine (1995) through to Jeunet's Le fabuleux destin d'Amélie Poulain (2000), Astérix et Obélix: Mission Cléopatre (2002) and Gothika (2003).Will Higbee's study is the first to explore of one of the most fascinating characters in French cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directors. 0aMotion picturesvReviews. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aFrench cultural exception youth culture.  aFrench popular culture.  aMathieu Kassovitz.  aauteur.  afilm director.  anew realism.  apostmodern social fables.  asocial realism.  ayouth audience.1 aHigbee, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614166840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141668/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles